Mop-up operations are under way in the Vereeniging area following localised flooding and damage. Several doctor’s rooms were flooded at Midvaal Private Hospital. eNCA’s Manqoba Mchunu filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Mop-up operations are underway in the Vereeniging area following localised flooding and damage on Friday. Several doctor's rooms were flooded at Midvaal Private Hospital. READ: Severe weather warning issued for the weekend Meanwhile, the South African Weather Services is warning of more possible storms and flooding in different parts of the country this weekend. KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng have been the worst hit by freak rain conditions this week.